Step--1
   build a Maven project
Step--2
   update properties file in pom.xml
Step--3 
  update dependencies
    a. put dependencies tag
       <dependencies>
        
      </dependencies>
      
     a1. https://mvnrepository.com/
         search Selenium Java--> get the latest version
           that will be look like this
             
              <dependencies>
				<dependency>
					<groupId>org.seleniumhq.selenium</groupId>
					<artifactId>selenium-java</artifactId>
					<version>4.15.0</version>
				</dependency>
							
    	   </dependencies>
    	   
    b. WebDriverManager dependency  (https://mvnrepository.com/)
    
      <!-- webdrivermanager -->
			<dependency>
			    <groupId>io.github.bonigarcia</groupId>
			    <artifactId>webdrivermanager</artifactId>
			    <version>5.6.2</version>
			</dependency>
			
	c. TestNG dependency  (https://mvnrepository.com/)
	
	          <dependency>
				    <groupId>org.testng</groupId>
				    <artifactId>testng</artifactId>
				    <version>7.7.0</version>
				    <scope>test</scope>
				</dependency>
 Step--4 
   Add TestNG plugins
      a. go to market place
      b. search TestNG
      c. install the plug-ins-->accept and trust all --restart eclipse
				
Step--4
  develop/update packages appropriately 
  update maven update
  
         
   